COMPONENT NAME: LKM File to SQL COMPONENT VERSION: 11.1.2.2 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 11.1.2.1 and above
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from an ASCII or EBCDIC File to any ISO-92 compliant database. - This module uses ODI Agent to read selected data from the source file and write the result in the target temporary table created dynamically.
Restrictions: - Source file must be physically accessible by ODI Agent. - All mappings must be executed on staging or target. - This Knowledge Module is NOT RECOMMENDED when using LARGE VOLUMES. Other specific modules using Bulk utilities (SQL*LOADER, BULK INSERT etc) are usually more efficient.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Perform basic cleanup on file after it is loaded. This will: - Distinct the rows - Remove empty rows
Note: this causes the temporary creation of a second temp table

<% if (cleanFile.equals("Y")) { %> create table <$ Z2 = "_CLEAN"; $><%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%><$ Z2 = ""; $> <% } else { %> create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%> <% } %> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]\t[DEST_WRI_DT] " + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL"), ",\n\t", "","")%> )

<% if (cleanFile.equals("Y")) { %> insert into <$ Z2 = "_CLEAN"; $><%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%><$ Z2 = ""; $> <% } else { %> insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%> <% } %> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]", ",
	", "","")%> ) values ( <% if (cleanFile.equals("Y")) { %> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "<? if ("[DEST_DT]".contains("CHAR")){?>SUBSTR(:[CX_COL_NAME],1,4000)<?} else {?>:[CX_COL_NAME]<?}?> ", ",
	", "","")%> <% } else { %> <%=odiRef.getColList("", ":[CX_COL_NAME]", ",
	", "","")%> <% } %> )

create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "W")%> as select distinct <%=odiRef.getColList("", "<? if (\u0022[DEST_DT]\u0022.contains(\u0022CHAR\u0022)){?>REPLACECHR(0,[CX_COL_NAME],CHR(13),'')<?} else {?>[CX_COL_NAME]<?}?> "+odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")+" [CX_COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "","")%> from <$ Z2 = "_CLEAN"; $><%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%><$ Z2 = ""; $> where not (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME] IS NULL", "\nand\t", "","")%>)
